</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81D0654DFFAD5310B9DBCDD811E2F87D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="key">
<key id="BD5B61F7FFAD5310B9DBCDD811E2F87D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyStep id="723E2E63FFAD5310B9DBCDD811E2F917" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCDD811E3F970" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" box="[136,1450,1696,1718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCDD811E3F970" box="[136,1450,1696,1718]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
1. Branches and foliage glabrous or hirtelous with whitish hairs; southeastern 
<collectingRegion id="0B0EF824FFAD5310BAF4CDD8101DF973" box="[935,1108,1696,1718]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Estado de Mexico</collectingRegion>
.................................... 
<taxonomicName id="0ECA4D45FFAD5310BC7CCDD811E3F970" box="[1327,1450,1696,1717]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Brongniartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="funiculata">
<emphasis id="FBBEEAD4FFAD5310BC7CCDD811E3F970" box="[1327,1450,1696,1717]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. funiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCDC511E2F917" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" box="[136,1451,1724,1746]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCDC511E2F917" box="[136,1451,1724,1746]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Branches and foliage hirtelous with whitish or brownish hairs or rarely glabrous; northern and central 
<collectingRegion id="0B0EF824FFAD5310BDF4CDC51148F917" box="[1191,1281,1725,1746]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
. .........................2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="723E2E63FFAD5310B9DBCDA111E2F880" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCDA111E2F8CE" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCDA111E2F8CE" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
2. Multi-stemmed shrub, several branched from the base; stipules (1.5–) 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BA26CDA1178CF92A" box="[885,965,1753,1775]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 mm</quantity>
wide; leaflets 6–12(–16) × (3–) 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BDA9CDA11107F92A" box="[1274,1358,1753,1775]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8 mm</quantity>
; southern face of the Neovolcanic Transversal Belt in the vicinity of Taxco, 
<collectingRegion id="0B0EF824FFAD5310BA18CD8E17EBF8CE" box="[843,930,1782,1803]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
.................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="0ECA4D45FFAD5310BC66CD8F11E2F8CE" box="[1333,1451,1782,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Brongniartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="abbottiae">
<emphasis id="FBBEEAD4FFAD5310BC66CD8F11E2F8CE" box="[1333,1451,1782,1804]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. abbottiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCC6B11E2F880" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCC6B11E2F880" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">- Single-stemmed shrub, normally with only a single main branch; stipules (3–)4–10(–18) mm wide; leaflet 11–30(–43) × 4–13(–15) mm; Sierra Madre del Sur in the vicinity of Chilpancingo and Eastern ward ...................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="723E2E63FFAD5310B9DBCC3511E2F87D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCC3511E2F8BB" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCC3511E2F8BB" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
3. Petals yellowish white; standard 9.9–11.6 × 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BB28CC351741F8A7" box="[635,776,1869,1890]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.305" metricValueMax="1.44" metricValueMin="1.17" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="13.05" valueMax="14.4" valueMin="11.7">11.7–14.4 mm</quantity>
; wing petals 8.4–11 × 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BAB2CC35101EF8A7" box="[993,1111,1869,1890]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.55" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="4.55" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="4.2">4.2–4.9 mm</quantity>
; keel petals 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BD9ECC34110DF8A7" box="[1229,1348,1868,1890]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.31" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.02" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="1.31" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.02">1.02–1.6 cm</quantity>
................ ........................................................................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="0ECA4D45FFAD5310BC6ECC1211E2F8BB" authorityName="R. Cruz-Duran, R. Bustamante &amp; Dorado" authorityYear="2022" box="[1341,1451,1897,1919]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Brongniartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alvarezii">
<emphasis id="FBBEEAD4FFAD5310BC6ECC1211E2F8BB" box="[1341,1451,1897,1919]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. alvarezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C97536C6FFAD5310B9DBCCFF11E2F87D" blockId="6.[136,1452,1696,1977]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<keyLead id="723B95F3FFAD5310B9DBCCFF11E2F87D" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
- Petals pink or pale pink, to salmon (in older herbarium flowers); standard 6.3–6.9 × 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BD52CCFE10CBF859" box="[1025,1154,1926,1948]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.8" metricValueMax="11.1" metricValueMin="8.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="9.8" valueMax="11.1" valueMin="8.5">8.5–11.1 mm</quantity>
; wing petals 7.1–7.6 × 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310BC30CCFE14B2F87D" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.4">3.4–3.9 mm</quantity>
; keel petals 
<quantity id="0E329B23FFAD5310B822CCDB15BDF87D" box="[369,500,1955,1976]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="7.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="0.75" valueMax="0.77" valueMin="0.73">0.73–0.77 cm</quantity>
.......................................................................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="0ECA4D45FFAD5310BC67CCDC11E2F87D" authorityName="Dorado, R. Cruz-Duran &amp; R. Bustamante" authorityYear="2022" box="[1332,1451,1955,1977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Brongniartia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis id="FBBEEAD4FFAD5310BC67CCDC11E2F87D" box="[1332,1451,1955,1977]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
